'''Jorge Luis Moreira Ferreira''' (born 1 February 1990) is a Paraguayan [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Portland Timbers]] on loan from Argentine [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]].

==Club career==
===2 de Mayo===
Born in [[Villarrica, Paraguay|Villarrica]], Moreira started his career with [[Club 2 de Mayo|2 de Mayo]], as a [[midfielder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/de-volante-a-mejor-lateral-de-nuestro-pais-1314637.html|title=De volante a mejor lateral de nuestro país|trans-title=From midfielder to the best full back of our country|publisher=[[ABC Color]]|language=es|date=10 December 2014|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref> Promoted to the first team in June 2009,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/deportes/moreira-lleno-expectativa-1186590.html|title=Moreira llenó expectativa|trans-title=Moreira fulfilled the expectations|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=29 June 2009|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref> he made his first team – and [[Paraguayan Primera División|Primera División]] – debut on 20 June, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Domingo Martínez (footballer)|Domingo Martínez]] in a 2–1 away loss against [[Club Nacional|Nacional]].

Moreira scored his first professional goal on 14 August 2009, netting the fourth in a 5–0 home routing of [[Tacuary]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/deportes/2-de-mayo-golea-a-tacuary-11669.html|title=2 de mayo golea a Tacuary|trans-title=2 de Mayo thrash Tacuary|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=15 August 2009|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref> He finished [[2009 Paraguayan Primera División season|his first senior season]] with two goals in 16 appearances.

===Libertad===
In December 2009, Moreira moved to [[Club Libertad|Libertad]] ahead of the ensuing campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/deportes/pittoni-y-nunez-volveran-a-tuyucua-54244.html|title=Pittoni y Núñez volverán a Tuyucuá|trans-title=Pittoni and Núñez will return to Tuyucuá|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=27 December 2009|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref> In 2011, after the injury of [[Carlos Bonet]], he was converted into a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]] by manager [[Gregorio Pérez]], and started to feature regularly in that position onwards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/es-mx/news/4838/paraguay/2013/02/12/3746700/moreira-a-gusto-como-lateral-derecho|title=Moreira, a gusto como lateral derecho|trans-title=Moreira, comfortable as a right back|publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|language=es|date=12 February 2013|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref>

Whilst at the club, Moreira won five league titles and scored six goals.

===River Plate===
On 21 July 2016, Moreira moved abroad for the first time in his career, joining [[Argentine Primera División]] side [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] after agreeing to a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/es-ar/news/13992/river/2016/07/21/25834322/jorge-moreira-firm%C3%B3-su-contrato-y-es-nuevo-jugador-de-river|title=Jorge Moreira firmó su contrato y es nuevo jugador de River|trans-title=Jorge Moreira signed his contract and is the new player of River|publisher=Goal|language=es|date=21 July 2016|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref> He made his debut abroad ten days later, starting in a 3–0 [[Copa Argentina]] home defeat of CS Rivadavia Venado Tuerto.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rosarioplus.com/enjuego/River-derroto-a-Sportivo-Rivadavia-de-Venado-Tuerto-por-3-a-0-20160801-0003.html|title=River derrotó a Sportivo Rivadavia de Venado Tuerto por 3 a 0|trans-title=River defeated Sportivo Rivadavia de Venado Tuerto by 3–0|publisher=Rosario Plus|language=es|date=1 August 2016|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref>

Moreira made his top tier debut on 28 August 2016, playing the full 90 minutes in a 4–1 home routing of [[Club Atlético Banfield|Banfield]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/cronica?juegoId=462906|title=River goleó a Banfield en el Monumental|trans-title=River thrashed Banfield at the Monumental|publisher=[[ESPN Deportes]]|language=es|date=28 August 2016|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club the following 27 April, netting the equalizer in a 2–1 win at [[C.S. Emelec|Emelec]], for [[2017 Copa Libertadores|the year]]'s [[Copa Libertadores]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/cronica/_/id/470379|title=River se recuperó, le ganó a Emelec y sigue con puntaje ideal
|trans-title=River recovered themselves, defeated Emelec and remain with the ideal number of points|publisher=ESPN Deportes|language=es|date=27 April 2017|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref>

In October 2017, Moreira suffered an injury which took him out of the [[2017 Copa Libertadores]] semifinals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tn.com.ar/deportes/esencial/river-jorge-moreira-se-lesiono-y-no-jugara-contra-lanus-por-la-copa-libertadores_829180|title=River: Jorge Moreira se lesionó y no jugará contra Lanús por la Copa Libertadores|trans-title=River: Jorge Moreira suffered an injury and will not play against Lanús for the Copa Libertadores|publisher=[[Todo Noticias]]|language=es|date=21 October 2017|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref> He then subsequently underwent surgery in his right [[knee]], being estimated to return under three months;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/2017/12/15/river-jorge-moreira-fue-operado-y-se-perdera-la-pretemporada/|title=River: Jorge Moreira fue operado y se perderá la pretemporada|trans-title=River: Jorge Moreira was operated and will miss the pre-season|publisher=Infobae|language=es|date=15 December 2017|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref> however, setbacks meant that he only could return in August 2018, nearly ten months from his last appearance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/river-plate/vuelve-moreira-confirmo-gallardo-titular-belgrano_0_SktBPf787.html|title=¡Vuelve Moreira!|trans-title=Moreira returns!|publisher=[[Olé (sports newspaper)|Olé]]|language=es|date=16 August 2018|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref>

===Portland Timbers===
On 20 February 2019, Moreira was acquired by [[Portland Timbers]] on loan from [[Club Atlético River Plate]] of Argentina.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timbers.com/post/2019/02/20/timbers-acquire-paraguayan-international-jorge-moreira-loan|title=Timbers acquire Paraguayan international Jorge Moreira on loan|language=en|date=20 February 2019|accessdate=20 February 2019}}</ref>

==International career==
Moreira represented [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] at [[Paraguay national under-17 football team|under-17]] and [[Paraguay national under-20 football team|under-20]] levels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.com.py/deportes/albirroja-sub-20--viajo-a-espana-19693.html|title=Albirroja Sub 20 viajó a España|trans-title=''Albirroja'' Under-20s travel to Spain|publisher=ABC Color|language=es|date=11 September 2009|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref> On 25 March 2010, he was first called up for [[Paraguay national football team|the full side]] by manager [[Gerardo Martino]] for a [[Exhibition match|friendly]] against [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rpctv.com/deportes/futbol/Paraguay-Sudafrica-titulares_0_244175661.html|title=Paraguay ante Sudáfrica sin los titulares|trans-title=Paraguay against South Africa without the starters|publisher=[[RPC-TV]]|language=es|date=25 March 2010|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref>

Moreira made his full international debut on 31 March 2010, replacing [[Jonathan Santana]] in the 1–1 draw at the [[Estadio Defensores del Chaco]] in [[Asunción]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultimahora.com/paraguay-empata-1-1-sudafrica-n309405.html|title=Paraguay empata 1–1 ante Sudáfrica|trans-title=Paraguay draw by 1–1 against South Africa|publisher=[[Última Hora (Paraguay)|Última Hora]]|language=es|date=31 March 2010|accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref>

